GateDocument.TextWithNodes: CALL FOR PAPERS The First International Symposium on Constructing Software Engineering Tools ( CoSET'99 ) 17 - 18 May 1999 A two-day workshop co-located with the International Conference on Software Engineering ( ICSE'99 ) , Los Angeles , USA , 16 - 22 May 1999 . Conference information : http : / / sunset . usc . edu / icse 99 / Symposium information : http : / / www . cis . unisa . edu . au / events / coset 99 / index . html Automated tools play an important role in the promotion and adoption of software engineering methods and processes , both within a particular organisation and within the software engineering community generally . The development of these tools is itself a significant software engineering task , requiring a considerable investment of time and resources . There are a large number of different kinds of automated software engineering tool variously known as Computer Aided Software Engineering ( CASE ) , Computer Aided Method Engineering ( CAME ) , Integrated Project Support Environments ( IPSE ) , Software Engineering Environments ( SEE ) , and meta - CASE tools . Although these tools differ in the particular methods , activities , and phases of the software development cycle to which they are applied , constructors of these tools often face similar implementation issues . Decisions about host computing platform , implementation language , conformance with standards and reference models , choice of repository , integration and interoperability mechanisms , and user interface style have to be made . The different strategies adopted by tool constructors when solving these tool development problems is the theme of this symposium . The symposium will be based around the participants' experience reports of constructing their SEE , IPSE , CASE , CAME , and meta - CASE tools . The purpose of the symposium is to bring together an international audience of researchers and practitioners with similar interests and experience , to exchange ideas , and to learn about different technologies and techniques for software engineering tool development . The symposium will focus principally on practical issues such as implementation languages and platforms , repository organization , tool integration and interoperability , and development approach . The symposium complements the themes and aims of the co-located ICSE conference , and it will be of interest to many practicing software engineers . We anticipate that this inaugural symposium will have several lasting and important outcomes , and it will establish a new forum for researchers and practitioners interested in software engineering tool construction . The CoSET'99 organisers will be editing a special issue of the Journal of Information and Software Technology ( IST ) , published by Elsevier , on the theme of Constructing Software Engineering Tools . A selection of papers from the symposium will be chosen for publication in the special issue , which is provisionally scheduled to appear in late 1999 . We are requesting two categories of symposium submission : - short papers , of typically 2000 - 4000 words ; - full papers , of 5000 - 6000 words plus figures / tables . Papers in both categories of submission will be fully refereed by the programme committee . The accepted short and full papers will appear in the Symposium Proceedings , but only full papers will normally be considered for inclusion in the journal special issue . Final selection of papers for the journal special issue will be completed shortly after the symposium . We request that authors format their submissions according to the instructions that can be found on the CoSET'99 web page . Submissions should be sent to the Symposium Chair as hard copy , or electronically as postscript or RTF files . Registration for the symposium is open to anyone interested in this area , but preference will be given to those with a submission if the symposium is oversubscribed . The ICSE'99 Secretariat is responsible for registration - see the ICSE'99 web page for more details . The Symposium programme will consist of : an introduction / overview session ; invited speakers ; sessions of experience report presentations and software demonstrations ; discussion and plenary sessions . Additionally , there will be a social event on the evening of 17 May .
